                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d535">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Walter S. Robertson</persName>, at Peiping</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-12">12 June
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>877. Yeh<note n="59" xml:id="d535fn59">Gen. Yeh Chien-ying, Chinese Communist
                        Commissioner of the Executive Headquarters at Peiping.</note> informs Chou
                    that Nationalist in Operations [Division] stated Tu Li-ming will resume advance,
                    attack, pursuit on 10th and then withdrew from meeting. Is this a fact? Rush
                    reply.</p>
            </div>
